RM  16121232
RT  DNA sequence of the Escherichia coli O103 O antigen gene cluster and
RT  detection of enterohemorrhagic E. coli O103 by PCR amplification of the
RT  wzx and wzy genes.
RA  Fratamico PM, DebRoy C, Strobaugh TP, Chen CY;
RL  Can J Microbiol. 2005;51:515-522.
CC  The E. coli O103 antigen structure has been determined [1], and the
CC  biosynthetic cluster analyzed [2]. The monomer unit is a linear
CC  pentasaccharide including one
CC  3-deoxy-3-(R)-3-hydroxybutyramido-D-fucose per unit. The cluster
CC  includes four glycosyltransferases (WbtDEFG), but accurate assignment
CC  of which enzyme carries out each reaction has not yet been determined.
CC  The needed reactions are: 1) aDGalNAc-(1->3)-bDGlcNAc, 2)
CC  aDGlcNAc-(1->4)-aDGalNAc, 3) bDFuc3NBu-(1->6)-aDGlcNAc, and 4)
CC  bDGlc-(1->2)-bDFuc3NBu.
**  Evidence for step 8 is also used for GP0912 (GUILD), GP0932, GP0947, GP0968 and GP0973.
